Jahanara.bcs345.purchases.business

Class Customer

  • java.lang.Object
    • Jahanara.bcs345.purchases.business.Customer

  • public class Customer
extends java.lang.Object
    The Customer class contains it's member variables and the definitions for it's default constructor, Get/Set methods, Write method, Read method, GetJSON method and an overridden toString method. The Customer class also reuses code by calling the Read, Write, GetJSON and overridden toString methods of the Address class within it's own Read, Write, GetJSON and overridden toString methods.
    Since:
    10/23/2016
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Niki Jahanara

      • Write

        public void Write(java.io.PrintStream ps)
        The Write method prints the values of the Customer class's member variables to a file by passing an instance of PrintStream into the method's parameter. The class also prints the values of the Address class's member variables to the same file by passing the instance of PrintStream to a call of Address's Write method.
        Parameters:
        ps - The instance of PrintStream.

      • Read

        public void Read(java.util.Scanner s)
        The Read method is passed an instance of Scanner in order to assign the values it reads on each line of the file, that the Write method generated, to each of the Customer class's member variables. The instance of Scanner is also passed into Address's Read method in order to assign the address data in the file to it's member variables.
        Parameters:
        s - The instance of Scanner.

      • GetJSON

        public java.lang.String GetJSON()
        The GetJSON method returns a concatenated string that formats the values of the member variables of Customer and Address into JSON format. Address's GetJSON method is called in order to include the Address class's JSON within the Customer class's JSON method.
        Returns:
        s Which contains the concatenated JSON string.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        The overridden toString method returns the Customer and Address member variable's values in a formatted string. The Address class's toString method is also called in order for the complete customer and address information to be returned by the method.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        s Which contains the values of the member variables in a formatted string.
